{
  "texts": [
    "The updated dynamic features D ′ f and static features S f are concatenated to form the full feature matrix C f ∈ R T ×B×(D+S).",
    "Messages are then propagated over the constructed hyperedges using the same mechanism:C ′ f = Propagate(C f, H).",
    "(6)The updated feature matrix C ′ f is split into enhanced dynamic features D e f and enhanced static features S e f. This mechanism enables bidirectional modality enhancement, where dynamic nodes benefit from static guidance while static nodes are simultaneously updated using dynamic context.",
    "Subsequently, as depicted in the right part of the RGB-Event Hypergraph guided Message Passing in Fig. 2, we leverage the Transformer to fuse temporal information for the enhanced dynamic features.",
    "After concatenation again, the features are processed by a self-attention mechanism to obtain the representation, which is then passed through an average pooling layer and a linear classification head to generate the final prediction."
  ]
}